{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6eb785f2-f96e-4c03-92e4-a85f184c5fb6","content":"Here's my proposed architecture and plan:\n\n---\n\n## RAG Q&A Feature — Architecture Plan\n\n### Overview\n\nAdd two capabilities to the existing .NET 10 Web API:\n\n1. **Ingestion pipeline** — reads markdown files from `Docs/`, splits them into chunks, generates embeddings, and stores them in a vector store.\n2. **Query endpoint** — accepts a user question, retrieves the most relevant chunks via semantic search, and sends them as context to an LLM to produce a grounded answer.\n\n---\n\n### High-Level Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────┐      ┌────────────┐      ┌────────────────┐\n│ Docs/*.md│─────▶│ Chunker    │─────▶│ Embedding Model│\n└──────────┘      └────────────┘      └───────┬────────┘\n                                              │\n                                              ▼\n                                      ┌──────────────┐\n                                      │ Vector Store │\n                                      └──────┬───────┘\n                                             │ (similarity search)\n┌──────────┐                                 │\n│ User Q   │────────────────────────────────▶│\n└──────────┘                                 ▼\n                                      ┌──────────────┐\n                                      │  LLM (Chat)  │◀── top-K chunks as context\n                                      └──────┬───────┘\n                                             │\n                                             ▼\n                                      ┌──────────────┐\n                                      │  Answer JSON │\n                                      └──────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Responsibility | Suggested Tech |\n|-----------|---------------|----------------|\n| **MarkdownLoader** | Read all `.md` files from `Docs/` | `Directory.EnumerateFiles` |\n| **TextChunker** | Split documents by heading/paragraph; ~300-500 token chunks with overlap | `Microsoft.SemanticKernel` text chunker or custom sliding-window |\n| **EmbeddingService** | Generate vector embeddings for each chunk | Azure OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` (or local ONNX model) |\n| **VectorStore** | Persist and query embeddings | In-process: **Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Connectors.InMemory** (swap for Qdrant/Azure AI Search in prod) |\n| **RetrievalService** | Semantic search: embed query → top-K nearest chunks | Cosine similarity via vector store |\n| **ChatService** | Compose prompt with retrieved context → call LLM | Azure OpenAI `gpt-4o` via Semantic Kernel |\n| **IngestionController** | `POST /api/ingest` — triggers re-ingestion | ASP.NET Controller |\n| **QueryController** | `POST /api/query` — accepts `{ question }`, returns `{ answer, sources[] }` | ASP.NET Controller |\n\n---\n\n### NuGet Packages to Add\n\n- `Microsoft.SemanticKernel` (orchestration, chunking, connectors)\n- `Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Connectors.InMemory` (vector store)\n- `Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Connectors.AzureOpenAI` (or `.OpenAI`)\n\n---\n\n### API Contract\n\n**POST /api/ingest**\n- Scans `Docs/`, chunks, embeds, stores. Returns `{ documentsProcessed, chunksStored }`.\n\n**POST /api/query**\n```json\n// Request\n{ \"question\": \"How do I install the product?\" }\n\n// Response\n{ \"answer\": \"Run `dotnet tool install --global product-cli`...\",\n  \"sources\": [\"getting-started.md#chunk-1\"] }\n```\n\n---\n\n### Chunking Strategy\n\n1. Split on `#` headings (each section = logical unit).\n2. If a section exceeds ~500 tokens, apply a sliding window (overlap ~50 tokens) to preserve context at boundaries.\n3. Store metadata per chunk: `fileName`, `heading`, `chunkIndex`.\n\n---\n\n### Configuration\n\nAdd to `appsettings.json`:\n```json\n\"Rag\": {\n  \"DocsPath\": \"Docs\",\n  \"ChunkMaxTokens\": 500,\n  \"ChunkOverlapTokens\": 50,\n  \"TopK\": 3,\n  \"EmbeddingModel\": \"text-embedding-3-small\",\n  \"ChatModel\": \"gpt-4o\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Considerations\n\n- **Startup ingestion**: optionally run ingestion on app start via `IHostedService` so the store is warm.\n- **Incremental updates**: hash file contents; skip unchanged files on re-ingest.\n- **Production swap**: replace in-memory store with Azure AI Search or Qdrant for persistence and scale.\n- **Grounding guardrail**: system prompt instructs the LLM to answer *only* from provided context and cite sources.\n\n---\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9fd24784-823a-4219-a861-fa6537f65048","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a good picture of the existing project. Let me create a plan for the RAG-based Q&A feature.","outputTokens":1277,"requestId":"C019:A78B9:20861CC:24C23E3:6A07D55F"},"id":"34b3c95a-d480-4798-8550-078c4869025a","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:24:54.947Z","parentId":"920041d4-15c3-4d64-af64-a340b7b82240"}
